content: This contribution hasn’t received enough positive votes from the community. The "SHORTEST" option has therefore been deactivated.

This is pretty good, but validator 2 (Cheaters !!!) caused me to only get 75% in my clash just now because it has a special Regexp character "?" that isn't tested in any in-game test cases. It would be good to add a question mark to one of the in-game tests to avoid disappointment from the validators hiding an edge case like this.

Also, you could make it clear in the statement that the Markov chains are case-sensitive.

✅ Approved the contribution.
Comment: This is a very interesting clash. Its statement is easy to understand, but coming up with a solution can be a good puzzle

✅ Approved the contribution.
Comment: A very fun and unique clash that relies on smart data structure creation and usage rather than just pounding out obvious code asap.

Comment: This is the second contribution I have approved. The statement is very clear, and test cases are very well defined. The solution is also very straightforward and demonstrates intelligence. Great job!
